# Punjab Group of Colleges (PGC) — Institute Overview
_Sample/dummy data for testing the multi-tenant RAG assistant. Not an official document._

Punjab Group of Colleges (PGC) is one of Pakistan's largest private networks of
colleges and schools, with campuses across most major cities in Punjab, KPK, and
Sindh. It offers intermediate (FSc/ICS/ICom), O/A-Level, and university-affiliated
programs, alongside its sister institutions (e.g., PGC University network, Air
University campuses under the group, and various professional colleges).

## Academic programs (sample)
- Pre-Medical, Pre-Engineering, and Computer Science (FSc/ICS)
- Commerce (ICom, B.Com pathways)
- O-Level and A-Level (Cambridge system)
- Entry-test preparation for MDCAT, ECAT, and NTS-based admissions

## Campus facilities (sample)
- Science and computer labs at all major campuses
- Merit-based scholarships for high-scoring students
- Hostel facilities at select campuses
- Career counseling and university placement support

## Sample student policies
- Attendance: minimum 75% attendance is required to sit for term exams.
- Uniform: students must wear the prescribed uniform on all campus days.
- Admission: based on matriculation/O-Level results plus an entry test for select
  programs.
- Fee submission: due within the first 10 days of each month; a late fee applies
  after the 10th.

## Contact
- Admissions helpline: sample-only, not a real number for this demo
- Website: pgc.edu.pk (for demo/testing purposes)